celebrates the
			 10th anniversary of the establishment of NATO Allied Command Transformation
			 (NATO ACT);

expresses
			 appreciation for the continuing and close partnership between the United States
			 Government and NATO to transform the alliance;

recognizes the
			 outstanding partnership between the local community in Norfolk, Virginia, and
			 NATO personnel assigned to ACT;

Whereas, on June 19, 2003, NATO’s Allied Command
			 Transformation (ACT), was formally established to increase military
			 effectiveness and prepare the Alliance for future security challenges;

Whereas the security of the United States and its NATO
			 allies have been enhanced by the establishment and continued work of NATO
			 ACT;

Whereas ACT provides state-of-the-art education, training,
			 and application of best practices and lessons learned from past operations, and
			 equips Alliance troops with the tools they need to win today’s wars;

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail:
 defense planning and develops
			 compatible equipment and common standards necessary to keep Alliance
			 capabilities aligned;

 endeavors to help the people of Afghanistan create the
			 conditions necessary for security and successful development and
			 reconstruction;

